# Project Memory Portal

## Goal

Make a project Brain render as a stable operator portal, not just a pile of notes: project memory at the top, then workstreams, sessions, turns, and tool-call receipts underneath.

`.brain/` remains the source/data layer. The SvelteKit/MDSvX Document Host is the product surface that can be served locally, on tailnet, or as static output when safe.

## Why this belongs in pi-notes

pi-notes already owns the reusable pieces:

- Document Host routing and rendering for `.brain/**/*.svx`
- project-local Brain components and `.brain/data/**` contracts
- Review Surface and Session Bridge concepts
- package-level guidance for Pi/Claude/Codex agents
- safe, readable MDSvX pages instead of opaque local databases

Product-specific bridges should emit or consume data/link contracts. They should not fork the portal stack.

## Dogfood source

`pi-discord-threads` is the first pressure test. Its Discord HUD/final-summary loop needs a stable memory link that stays useful across turns and points into a richer project/session history surface.

The bridge-side tracer bullet should produce curated session-memory data and a stable link object. pi-notes should later generalize the portal routes, components, and session-history adapters.

## Initial shape

- Project portal route: stable entrypoint for the repo Brain.
- Workstream index: groups related Discord/Pi sessions, project notes, decisions, and open loops.
- Session page: curated summary plus links to raw Pi JSONL truth where available.
- Turn drilldown: prompt, final answer, tool-call receipts, checks, and risks.
- Component kit: source-copyable MDSvX components for summaries, timelines, receipts, decisions, risks, and next actions.

## Boundaries

- Do not treat raw chat transcripts as the human artifact.
- Do not store private machine paths, secrets, customer data, or raw Discord IDs in public/static outputs.
- Do not make product-specific adapters define core portal architecture.
- Do not overwrite project Brain content when adding generated session data.

## Next slice

Define the shared data contract for project/workstream/session/turn/tool-call records, then render a minimal read-only portal view from `.brain/data/**`.
